{
 "name": "RPlog_Unexpected_Treasure",
 "title": "Unexpected Treasure: The Map of Darius Nul",
 "summary": "In the courtyard of the University of Corellia, the Horansi Jedi Sinjon Teague introduces his rough-edged acquaintance Captain Nerik to the scholar-smuggler Paul Nighman, hoping Paul can translate an ancient scroll Nerik carries. Paul recognizes it at once as a genuine, painstakingly copied star chart in archaic Corellian--a treasure map supposedly leading to the lost hoard of the famous Corellian pirate Darius Nul. Reluctant to be cut out, Nerik agrees to split the find, and Paul authenticates the parchment with his instruments before puzzling out its hidden constellations by folding the map, revealing the trail leads to the Imperial-held world of Athaniss, with the treasure resting underwater along the bottom of its north sea. The three agree to team up, acquiring diving gear and contacts on Caspar, and part ways to rendezvous there--Paul keeping the map, with Sinjon to vouch for him.",
